OL,3,CConcerns island air fare rises could
OL,4,Cthreaten tourism economy
OL,6,FResident Barbara Benfield says: "Maybe
OL,7,FAlderney ought to put pressure on the
OL,8,FBritish government, because it's clear
OL,9,Fthat the relationship and the
OL,10,FBailiwick itself is no longer working
OL,11,Fproperly."
OL,13,FOther islanders fear the increased air
OL,14,Ffares will discourage people from
OL,15,Fconsidering the island as a holiday
OL,16,Fdestination.
